	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>Strange</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11"></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Aug 6th 10:01 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=/db/poster.html?user=81236><span id= >Gutto</span></a><br><span id=notbold>2 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>So yesterday I decided to give this a go. i started out with the Dragoon Dirk. Camped Dorn in No Ro for maybe 45 min. had to kill him three times. He dropped it the third time. BTW, Dorn has a 15 min spawn rate. Next went to Innoth Swamp since I was right there to get my alligator skin. This I was worried about b/c of all the post here about how hard it was to get one. Walked right in and got a skin on my second kill. Next I went to North Karana. Killed a half dozen Rabig Grizzlies and one droped my skin. So I went to Everfrost and there I just found a newbie that had been hunting in the area and gave him a chuck of change for a Polar Bear Skin. At this point, I had traveled all over Antonica and didn't feel like looking for a common Polar Bear in Everfrost. Very confusing zone that's easy to get lost in. I got all the required components in about 4-6 hours. I spent all my time running around. That's what took so long. My problem is that I can't get the Marshall to talk to me about the quest. I'm a Level 20 Halfling Druid. He mentions the LeatherFoot raiders but wont mention the quest. I'm not about to get burned so I'm not giving him the items until he mentions the quest. Any ideas? I find this to be frustrating. Played 6 hours...Got all the stuff and now it's Pay Up time. </p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Gutto <br>Halfling Druid - Xegony</td></tr>
